Onyekachukwu Meluwa, Warri Gunmen suspected to be hired assassins reportedly killed the chairman of the Peoples Democratic Party in Ward 4 (Olomu Ward 1), Mr Paul Onomuakpokpo, in the Ughelli South Local Government Area of Delta State on Wednesday night. Our correspondent learnt that the incident occurred along Ogoni Road, near the palace of Ohworode of Olomu Kingdom. A source said, ‘’The gunmen suspected to be assassins ambushed the deceased at about 7pm and rained bullets on him. ‘’The victim (PDP chairman) died on the spot. ‘’The gunmen fired into the air repeatedly until they ensured that he was dead. “The killers riddled the deceased’s Toyota Camry (Spider) he was driving at the time with bullets.’’ The Police Public Relations Officer, Delta State Command, Onome Onovwakpoyey, a Deputy Superintendent of Police, confirmed the incident. Copyright PUNCH.
